description: This 48-page double-sized first issue tells the story of a young hero, Cameron Williams, as he is thrust into the world of secret societies and super spy wars. While trying to juggle college, a blossoming relationship with his childhood dream-girl, and keeping his parents out of harm's way, Cameron realizes that his life will never be the same again. But is the change for the better, or worse?

In a matter of 48 hours, Cameron Williams' life has been turned upside down and flipped inside out. The cybernetic-mercenary organization called ?The Cause" has captured Cameron's parents in an effort to draw him out for his capture; hoping to exploit him for his genetic make-up to create more "EON Soldiers". Will they succeed? What are Morrow's motivations for taking down "The Cause"?

In the exciting conclusion of this three part debut, Cameron Williams must push his abilities to its limits and to save his parents that are being captive by The Cause. Will Cameron and Morrow find them in time? Will Cameron's best be enough to rescue both his parents and destroy The Cause for good?

deck: Issue 1 of 6, superhero force The Echelon set up suspicious evaluation centers that stir an old hero from retirement.

volume.name: Warcraft: Trilogiya Solnechnogo rodnika. Kollektsionnoye izdaniye

description: Lana Lang and Lois Lane, together again! Of course, this time they're battling local warlords who want to destroy the Angel of Plateau's rescue operation.
name: Valkyrie Part 3

description: The classic tale that exploded into comics shops in the early 1980s is collected for the first time in hardcover! Featuring a new cover by acclaimed artist Brian Bolland, this deluxe, oversized volume collects the twelve-issue series in its entirety, along with bonus materials including never-before-seen preliminary artwork by Bolland and developmental material from writer Mike W. Barr!
name: Deluxe Edition

description: For the first time ever, DC's classic 3-issue epic is collected in hardcover. In this tale of Cold War paranoia, the spaceship carrying the infant Superman lands in the 1950s Soviet Union, where he grows up to become a symbol of Soviet power.
name: Deluxe Edition

volume.name: Superman: Red Son: The Deluxe Edition

description: Ryo Takatsuki thinks he's just a normal kid in high school, but strange things start happening--the new guy in school is trying to kill him; secret agents with high-powered weapons and modified limbs show up and start hunting him down; then his own body begins to transform into something grotesque and out of control. In order to find out what is going on, Ryo must come face to face with the underground world of secret organizations, fierce mercenary agents, and the secrets of his own mysterious past...
name: The First Revelation: The Awakening

description: Ryo finds other kids out there that are just like him and together they attempt to uncover why this was done to them. To get to the truth, they must come face to face with underground organizations, fierce mercenary agents, and a sublimely powerful new tehnology...
name: The Frist Revelation: Egrigori

description: Hayato Shingu must confront the horrors of his past as he, Ryo, and Takeshi return to his village which was destroyed by Egrigori ten years ago. Egrigori has subsequently turned the place into a research lab dealing in nanotechnology and human experimentation. But before they can find out any more, the Arms kids must survive a battle against The Crimson Triad, a high-tech super-agent group known for their ruthless bloodlust.
name: The First Revelation: Jabberwock

description: Caught in the crossfire of a powerful secret organization and its cybernetic assassins, their friend Katsumi has disappeared before their very eyes. When the Arms kids vow to rescue her no matter what the cost, they encounter Kei Kuruma, a dead ringer for Katsumi and a girl with a most deadly look in her eye...
name: The Second Revelation: Evil Eye

description: The X-Army is the latest group of super-agents that are after Ryo and the other Arms kids. Up against these agents with powers of super strength, super vision, and twisting telekinesis, it looks like the Arms kids have more than they can handle.... That is until the raging and out of control Jabberwock comes out from within Ryo. Will anybody be safe?
name: The Second Revelation: The X-Army

description: From the creative team of "Formerly Known as the Justice League," in the comedic tradition of "Formerly Known as the Justice League!" Ever wonder about the whole parallel universe thing? Ever fantasize about meeting up with a variant version of yourself? Maybe a superhero variant? Pretty cool, huh? Ever stop to consider what might happen if this superhero version of yourself moved in with you and started hitting on your girlfriend? Still think it's cool? Oh, and there's a universe-destroying super villain gunning for your superhero self, did we forget to mention that?
name: Over the Looking Glass

description: As they attempt to uncover the mysteries of their past, the latest group of superagents to come after them are the chillingly cruel Red Caps with their most deadly strategy--the vicious "snark hunt." Desperate and chased to the brink of death, Hayato Shingu undergoes a transformation of sublime proportions.
name: The Second Revelation: Knight

description: In a desperate attempt to dispose of a neutron bomb on the verge of exploding, something is triggered within Takeshi's body which causes him to transform into his ultimate form...
name: The Second Revelation: White Rabbit

description: Their desperate quest to uncover the secrets of their pasts takes them to a tiny desert town in Arizona called Gallows Bell. The horrifying reality that awaits them there could be more shocking than they can handle!
name: The Third Revelation: Gallows Bell

description: It's the attack of the Keith clones! In this volume the mysterious organization Egrigori sends out Keith Silver to hunt down the Arms kids. But will Ryo and the others survive when Silver goes completely beserk?!
name: The Third Revelation: Agni

description: The Arms Kids' quest to uncover the truth about their past takes them from Japan to a cowpoke town in Arizona called Gallows Bell. There, they come face to face with an elite group of special forces called Team Epsilon. Ryo and the others soon learn that this viciously wicked squadron hasn't earned its nickname "Genocide Force" for nothing. To make matters worse, enter a new enemy Arms called "The Mad Hatter," with powers that verge on the sublime.
name: The Third Revelation: Mars

description: The Arms kids go to New York where Ryo's friend Katsumi is being held prisoner. Little do they know the nightmare that awaits them there--a secret weapon who goes by the name Karunagi!
name: The Fourth Revelation: Nightmare

description: The Arms kids hit the Big Apple! But Keith Green has dispatched the fiercest bunch of assassins around to bring them down! And poor Takeshi's gotten hit so hard, he gets sent toâ¦wonderland!
name: The Fourth Revelation: Wonderland

description: Takeshi, injured and in a coma, takes a bizarre journey through his unconscious mind and learns about the origins of Egrigori and what Arms really are. Meanwhile, Ryo discovers more about the true nature of the Jabberwock--but can he face up to the fact that the monster inside him is meant purely for destruction?
name: The Fourth Revelation: Birth

description: The secret origin of Arms, the nefarious plans of Egrigori and the Keith series of clone superleaders all seem to be connected to a massive computer system called Alice. But the Arms kids discover Alice is much more than just a bunch of chips and semiconductors!
name: The Fourth Revelation: Icon

description: Vowing to protect the world at any cost, Ryo and the others set out to destroy Alice, the massive Al computer that lies at the heart of Egrigori's nefarious plans!
name: The Fourth Revelation: Fortress

description: The Arms kids have entered Carillon Tower, headquarters of Egrigori, the organization that aspires to engineer the future of mankind with a race of cyborgs. But as the kids try to destroy the organization's facilities, they run up against the Next--an advanced series of cyborg soldiers stronger than anything Ryo and his friends have ever faced before!
name: The Fourth Revelation: Next

description: The Arms kids continue their battle deeper into Carillon Tower in order to reach Alice, a supercomputer intent on wiping out humankind. But now they must confront the Keith Series--mutants with powers equal to their own. And they find that one small error in self-control can cause an Arms meltdown, destroying their enemies, their allies, and the entire city around them!
name: The Fourth Revelation: Meltdown

description:
Ryo, Hayato, Takeshi and Kei are Arms--kids implanted with nanotech limb enhancements that cause them to transform into grotesquely deformed and out-of-control superweapons.

After coming through many fierce battles, Ryo arrives at the supercomputer Alice's location ready to finally settle things once and for all! But despite Ryo's amazing physical powers, he finds he's no match for Keith Black's powers of mind control. Instead of enemies, Ryo and his friends must fight the illusions in their own minds!
name: The Fourth Revelation: Remembrance

description: The battle in Manhattan draws to a climax, as Keith White launches "Program Jabberwock" on a terrible path of destruction. Ryo and the other Arms are thrust into the strange parallel dimension "Wonderland," where Ryo must fight the consciousness of the Jabberwock itself before it reduces the real world to ruins.
name: The Fourth Revelation: Pandemonium

description: The power of the Arms' superweapons has disappeared, leaving them free to lead normal lives. But their newfound peace is shattered when Katsumi is abducted by Keith White. Egrigori is back--this time to put Program Bandersnatch into effect. Now Ryo and the gang must go up against their Egirgori foes barehanded to get Katsumi back!
name: The Last Revelation: Bandersnatch

description: Program Bandersnatch has engaged, and Katsumi's power creates an unnatural winter in Tokyo, a cold hell in which no one can survive for long. Bereft of their ARMS powers, Ryo and the others strive to stop the countdown to destruction. Just as they are almost crushed by despair, a light appears in the darkness. But will this "light" be enough?
name: The Last Revelation: Shining

description: Ryo, Hayato and Takeshi race to stop the Bandersnatch from destroying mankind as it rampages through Tokyo. Together with Ryo's father Iwao, they gather their strength for one last battle. But the modulated Arms they're up against are more formidable than they bargained for. Can they stop the Bandersnatch's countdown to destruction?
name: The Last Revelation: Return

description: Suske and Wiske are accidentally transported to an alternate timeline where Krimson has conquered the island Amoras. The news of their disappearance hits those left behind very hard. And in this timeline, Barabas is kidnapped by Krimson who has built a copy of the Teletijdmachine (a time travel machine). Krimson wants to force Barabas to make it work.
name: Suske

volume.name: Paleo Tales of the Late Cretaceous

description: When a crime boss' daughter turns up missing, who's he gonna to call? Boss Karate Black Guy Jones, that's who! The two-fisted, karate chopping, crime solving machine is kicking ass and taking names from the gutters of Baltimore all the way to the streets of Rome. No dog's too big for this cat to take down! Mimes, clowns, drunks, pizza, donkeys, pornography, gambling! Vatican Hustle has it all!
name: GN

description: Simon Adams is certainly not one of those dead-beat dads. Watch him stagger through the pee, the poo, and the puke in a sleep-deprived haze. Observe as he becomes a second class citizen in his X-chromosome controlled domicile. And feel as Simon tries to juggle career ambitions and his family in an act worthy of the best circus performers. No, you're not alone; this is what it's like for everyone.
name: TPB

description: Dive deeper into the supernatural world of Wren, the peculiar protagonist hell bent on sending her ghostly houseguests back to the afterlife. Will she succeed in ridding herself of her rambunctious roommates, or will they annoy her to death?

person_credits.name: Garry Trudeau
person_credits.role: writer, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description: Adapted from historian Howard Zinn's bestselling grassroots history of the United States, the story of America in the world is told in comics form! Now Zinn, historian Paul Buhle, and cartoonist Mike Konopacki have collaborated to retell, in vibrant comics form, a most immediate and relevant chapter of A People's History - the centuries-long story of America's actions in the world. Narrated by Zinn, this version opens with the events of 9/11 and then jumps back to explore the cycles of U.S. expansionism from Wounded Knee to Iraq, stopping along the way at World War I, Central America, Vietnam, and the Iranian revolution. The book also follows the story of Zinn, the son of poor Jewish immigrants, from his childhood in the Brooklyn slums to his role as one of America's leading historians.
name: HC/SC
